          <h1>Tree-like peonies</h1>
          <p>History</p>
          <p>Cultivated in China for over 1,500 years, tree peonies became the favorite flower of emperors during the Tang Dynasty. Later adopted in Japan, they spread to Europe in the 19th century.</p>
          <p>In China, they symbolize wealth, honor, and nobility — known as the "king of flowers." In Japan, they represent bravery and good fortune. Woody stems, huge silky blooms, and a lifespan of over 100 years make them unforgettable.</p>
        </div>

